verses.verse: A Psalm of David. Ascribe <S%H3051><s%> unto Jehovah <S%H3068><s%>, O ye sons of the mighty <S%H1121><s%>, Ascribe <S%H3051><s%> unto Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> glory <S%H3519><s%> and strength <S%H5797><s%>.
Ascribe <S%H3051><s%> unto Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> the glory <S%H3519><s%> due unto his name <S%H8034><s%>; Worship <S%H7812><s%> Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> in holy <S%H6944><s%> array <S%H1927><s%>.

The voice <S%H6963><s%> of Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> is upon the waters <S%H4325><s%>: The God <S%H410><s%> of glory <S%H3519><s%> thundereth <S%H7481><s%>, Even Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> upon many <S%H7227><s%> waters <S%H4325><s%>.
The voice <S%H6963><s%> of Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> is powerful <S%H3581><s%>; The voice <S%H6963><s%> of Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> is full of majesty <S%H1926><s%>.

The voice <S%H6963><s%> of Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> breaketh <S%H7665><s%> the cedars <S%H730><s%>; Yea <S%H3068><s%>, Jehovah breaketh <S%H7665><s%> in pieces the cedars <S%H730><s%> of Lebanon <S%H3844><s%>.
He maketh them also to skip <S%H7540><s%> like a calf <S%H5695><s%>; Lebanon <S%H3844><s%> and Sirion <S%H8303><s%> like a young <S%H1121><s%> wild-ox <S%H7214><s%>.
The voice <S%H6963><s%> of Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> cleaveth <S%H2672><s%> the flames <S%H3852><s%> of fire <S%H784><s%>.
The voice <S%H6963><s%> of Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> shaketh <S%H2342><s%> the wilderness <S%H4057><s%>; Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> shaketh <S%H2342><s%> the wilderness <S%H4057><s%> of Kadesh <S%H6946><s%>.

The voice <S%H6963><s%> of Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> maketh the hinds <S%H355><s%> to calve <S%H2342><s%>, And strippeth <S%H2834><s%> the forests <S%H3295><s%> bare <S%H1964><s%>: And in his temple everything saith <S%H559><s%>, Glory <S%H3519><s%>.
Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> sat <S%H3427><s%> as King at the Flood <S%H3999><s%>; Yea <S%H3068><s%>, Jehovah sitteth <S%H3427><s%> as King <S%H4428><s%> for ever <S%H5769><s%>.
Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> will give <S%H5414><s%> strength <S%H5797><s%> unto his people <S%H5971><s%>; Jehovah <S%H3068><s%> will bless <S%H1288><s%> his people <S%H5971><s%> with peace <S%H7965><s%>.
